**The poster for the upcoming study-abroad workshop is designed to capture the spirit of conquering the race to top US universities. The overall theme centers on the art of building a winning extracurricular profile and positioning oneself for admission to the most elite schools. To convey this message, the poster features a bold and dynamic image of a runner sprinting towards the finish line, overlaid with a stylized graphic of an American flag. The runner's determination and focus represent the drive and discipline required to succeed in the competitive world of American higher education. Meanwhile, the flag symbolizes the opportunities and values that define the US academic experience, from academic rigor and innovation to diversity and free expression. In the foreground, the poster highlights the main topic of the workshop, which is how to craft a standout extracurricular profile that showcases one's unique skills, passions, and accomplishments. The tagline, "Join the race to the top with our expert guidance," reinforces the idea that with the right tools and strategies, anyone can achieve their dreams of studying at a top US university. The overall color scheme is red, white, and blue, to evoke a sense of patriotism and aspiration, as well as to tie in with the American flag motif.
